post_text:
At last night's School Board meeting, the Board voted to extend Plan C, which is remote instruction for all of our students, through the end of the first nine weeks.
The first nine weeks ends on October 16. At the next School Board meeting, they will analyze the health data and discuss what will be the best course of action moving forward for the second nine weeks. Thank you for your understanding, continued support, and cooperation. The health and safety of all of the Thomasville City School students is always our top priority.

post_text: Although we are beginning the year in Plan C for remote learning, Thomasville City Schools will be offering a fully virtual option for our families who would like to remain remote for a longer period of time. The Thomasville Remote Academy for Innovative Learning (TRAIL) program is designed for highly motivated learners in K-12 who desire an alternative to the traditional classroom environment due to COVID-19 or are seeking flexible instructional options for any variety of reasons. TCS families as well as charter, private, and homeschool families are invited to participate in this program. Students will be enrolled in their assigned schools and will receive instruction from certified TCS teachers. Technology is available from the district for those families who would need it to participate. For more information, frequently asked questions, or to apply to be a TRAILblazer, visit https://www.tcs.k12.nc.us/apps/pages/TRAIL. Applications for TRAIL are due by 12:00 noon on Friday, July 31.

post_text:
Superintendent Dr. Catherine Gentry and the Board of Education Chairperson, James Carmichael, today announce specific plans for reopening schools in the TCS district.
Absent a change in public health data, and/or a change mandated from the governor, Thomasville City Schools will open the 2020-2021 school year under the state’s “Plan
C”. Plan C is the fully remote option.
Read the full press release on the district website at https://bit.ly/30mPLLi

post_text: Governor Cooper announced today a statewide plan to start school under Plan B which is a hybrid plan (part face to face and part virtual/remote). In addition, districts are able to choose the option to go with Plan C, which is full remote/virtual learning. Our district has been working on specifics for each option. We will also provide a fully virtual option regardless of our entry plan. Our board of education will be meeting virtually on Thursday, July 16, 2020 at 6pm. The link for the meeting will be available on our website and social media outlets. The purpose of this meeting will be a final/specific decision on opening our district that meets the specific needs of our students and staff. Additional information will be provided following the meeting and throughout next week as plans are finalized. We appreciate your continued support, understanding, and patience during this important time. Our goal is to make informed decisions that best support all of Bulldog Nation.

post_text: The Drivers Education Department has not received DPI formal guidelines for face to face or virtual summer/fall class options. As soon as the guidelines are released, Drivers Education staff will develop a plan for classes in the fall. Students who have completed and passed the February/March 2020 class will be scheduled for Behind the Wheel training as soon as DPI releases recommendations and guidelines on how to complete the training following required safety measures. If you have any questions please feel free to call the Transportation Office at 336-474-4173.

post_text: Congratulations to our "Of the Year" Winners:

post_text:
On Tuesday, May 28, 2019 our office was informed of an inappropriate picture that was placed in a collage on the Thomasville High School yearbook cover. Yearbooks were distributed to a few selected members of the student body and staff. Upon notice of the inappropriate picture, all yearbooks were collected. The theme of this year’s book, “A Blast to the Past” looked back at the history of Thomasville High School, and used several photos from previous yearbooks. A picture used from the class of 1968, had the words “Go Dogs” being held in front
of the Confederate flag. Swift action is being taken to remove the picture from all yearbook covers and provide new books to students and staff. We apologize for such an egregious error and vow to have a system in place to prevent such mistakes from happening again.

post_text:
Please be advised that we are in an area under a weather advisory until tomorrow morning. We will continue to monitor conditions overnight and into the AM.
If conditions require a delay or closure, we will make that call by 6am on Wednesday, January 23, 2019. Please stay tuned for updates via social media, website, robocall and TV. Thank you!

Favor sepan que estamos en un área bajo advertencia de mal clima hasta mañana. Vamos a continuar a observar el clima durante la noche y la mañana. Si las condiciones requieren de un retraso o cierre escolar, haremos un llamado para las 6am el miércoles 23 de enero, 2019. Favor de mantenerse al tanto de actualizaciones por medios de nuestros medios sociales, sito en línea, y llamada y televisión. ¡Gracias!
